        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-7095",
        "content": "When the Egyptologists, Assyriologists, archeologists, and anthropologists showed that man had reached a far advanced stage of civilization long before the six thousand years given as the age of the earth, their efforts were ridiculed by the clergy, and these scientists were forced to bring their findings before the world in the face of the well known methods of ecclesiastical opposition.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-normal",
